<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-04T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-04T12:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">365.1121 Cimador, Guido/4:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Trieste (<persName type="from">Winslow</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting
                                        Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Trieste</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-04T18:00:00+01:00">August
                                        4, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received August 8—5:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s August 3, 6 p.m. Cimador favorably known to and
                                registered at Consulate was arrested June 3rd for political and
                                moral reasons and is now confined on island near Naples.
                                Unofficially but reliably informed that real reasons for arrest were
                                his actions in placing flowers on bier of dead anarchist and
                                accompanying body to grave. I will visit Carnico in the near future
                                to make investigation. Embassy informed.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Winslow</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>